dataIdInfo.idPurp: These layers are intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [These data are intended for use at a scale of 1:12000 or smaller. The data are designed for reference mapping and labelling.]
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data layer represents roads for Portage County, Wisconsin in 2015. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Portage_Roads_2015.gdb. [The Centerline data set is a vector representation of center of pavement in the County of Portage, Wisconsin. The centerlines are digitized from 1:12000 digital orthophotography or entered by coordinate geometry.]
